To retrieve all users, I would create a GET endpoint because GET is the standard HTTP method for fetching data.

Example using FastAPI:

from fastapi import FastAPI

app = FastAPI()

@app.get("/users")
def get_users():
    return {"message": "Return all users"}

If using SQL, the query would be:

SELECT * FROM users;

In a real application, I would use SQLAlchemy or another ORM to execute the query and return the results as JSON. I would also include proper exception handling and pagination when the table contains many records.
